WEBVTT

00:02.001 --> 00:05.036
     Cheers <i>is filmed</i>           
 <i>before a live studio audience.</i> 

00:09.959 --> 00:11.325
Oh! Oh!                         

00:11.360 --> 00:14.079
( <i>gasping</i> )                     

00:14.113 --> 00:17.082
Sam, I think Carla              
has a drink order.              

00:18.784 --> 00:19.917
            Sweetheart,         
            are you all right?  

00:19.952 --> 00:21.970
Sammy, I think this could be it.

00:22.004 --> 00:23.771
 I think the twins are coming.  

00:23.806 --> 00:24.840
                Oh. Ooh, ooh!   

00:24.874 --> 00:25.841
( <i>groans</i> )                      

00:25.875 --> 00:26.842
            What do you know?   

00:26.876 --> 00:28.109
                The Sixers are  
                in town tonight.

00:28.144 --> 00:30.611
        Isn't it amazing        
        how Carla's labor pains 

00:30.646 --> 00:34.082
        always seem to coincide 
        with Celtic home games? 

00:34.116 --> 00:35.683
Hey, hey, hey, hey!             

00:35.718 --> 00:37.602
         Wait a minute.         

00:37.637 --> 00:40.388
Now, you think                  
that I would exploit            

00:40.422 --> 00:42.590
this beautiful thing            
called motherhood               

00:42.624 --> 00:46.394
just to go                      
to some stupid basketball game? 

00:46.428 --> 00:49.414
          ( <i>groaning</i> )          

00:49.449 --> 00:51.149
         I'm insulted!          

00:51.183 --> 00:52.200
     Carla, I'm not falling     
    for it this time.           

00:52.234 --> 00:53.301
You can scream till you shatter 

00:53.335 --> 00:54.602
        every glass in this bar,

00:54.636 --> 00:55.770
 but you're not going anywhere. 

00:55.804 --> 00:57.522
        ( <i>groans</i> )              

00:57.556 --> 00:58.640
            Sweetheart,         
            you're just going   

00:58.674 --> 01:00.775
        to have to give birth   
        right here in the bar.  

01:00.809 --> 01:02.577
            Come on.            
     It won't be that bad.      

01:02.612 --> 01:05.129
     Remember, the last kid     
 you had here was no big deal.  

01:05.164 --> 01:06.364
All you had to do               
was a little                    

01:06.398 --> 01:08.582
            snip-snip           
            and a quick mop-up  

01:08.617 --> 01:09.734
and you were right back         
on your feet.                   

01:09.769 --> 01:11.085
( <i>groaning</i> )                    

01:11.120 --> 01:12.453
                Let me call you 
                a cab, Carla.   

01:12.487 --> 01:14.989
It's all right.                 
I got one waiting.              
Thank you.                      

01:15.024 --> 01:16.441
            Hey, uh, there      
            wouldn't happen     
            to be another seat  

01:16.476 --> 01:17.576
        in the delivery room,   
        would there?            

01:17.610 --> 01:19.243
No, no.                         
There are only seats            
for me and Eddie, Sam.          

01:19.278 --> 01:20.311
                    Oh, come on.

01:20.346 --> 01:22.297
      Maybe next... child.      

01:22.331 --> 01:24.132
        ( <i>groans</i> )              

01:25.518 --> 01:29.454
        ( <i>piano plays</i> )         

01:29.488 --> 01:31.906
    ¶ Making your way           
      in the world today ¶      

01:31.941 --> 01:35.126
¶ Takes everything you've got   

01:35.161 --> 01:37.862
        ¶ Taking a break        
    from all your worries ¶     

01:37.896 --> 01:41.098
¶ Sure would help a lot         

01:41.133 --> 01:46.304
      ¶ Wouldn't you like       
         to get away? ¶         

01:46.338 --> 01:49.190
  ¶ Sometimes you want to go    

01:49.224 --> 01:54.562
    ¶ Where everybody           
    knows your name ¶           

01:54.596 --> 01:59.234
¶ And they're always glad       
        you came ¶              

01:59.268 --> 02:01.502
        ¶ You want to be        
      where you can see ¶       

02:01.536 --> 02:04.239
         ¶ Our troubles         
    are all the same ¶          

02:04.273 --> 02:09.676
¶ You want to be where everybody
    knows your name ¶           

02:09.711 --> 02:11.863
        ¶ You want to go        
      where people know ¶       

02:11.897 --> 02:14.615
  ¶ People are all the same     

02:14.650 --> 02:18.519
     ¶ You want to go where     
  everybody knows your name. ¶  

